<node CREATED="1576216631093" ID="ID_682166398" MODIFIED="1576216631093" TEXT="How I/O virtualization works. In I/O virtualization a virtual device is substituted for its physical equivalent such as a network interface card or host bus adapter . Aside from simplifying server configurations this setup has cost implications by reducing the electric power drawn by these devices." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631093" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_644942318" LINK="https://cacm.acm.org/magazines/2012/1/144808-i-o-virtualization/fulltext" MODIFIED="1576216631093" TEXT="I/O Virtualization | January 2012 | Communications of the ACM">
