<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_1768333795" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Before you can upload data to Amazon S3 you must create a bucket in one of the AWS Regions to store your data in. After you create a bucket you can upload an unlimited number of data objects to the bucket. A bucket is owned by the AWS account that created it. By default you can create up to 100 buckets in each of your AWS accounts. " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631111" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_771551485" LINK="https://intellipaat.com/blog/what-is-amazon-s3/" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="What is Amazon S3 tutorial - Creating a AWS S3 bucket ">
<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_1710422861" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Amazon S3 is a storage that can be maintained and accessed over the Internet. In this Amazon S3 tutorial you will learn about what is Amazon S3 and its concepts how to create an AWS S3 bucket and more." />
