<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_1854894826" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Create an Amazon S3 Bucket&#194;&#182;. The name of an Amazon S3 bucket must be unique across all regions of the AWS platform. The bucket can be located in a specific region to minimize latency or to address regulatory requirements." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631111" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_663558480" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/s3-bucket-migrate-region/" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Re-create Amazon S3 Bucket in Another AWS Region">
<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_596793840" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="You cant migrate an existing S3 bucket into another AWS Region. Instead create a new bucket in the destination Region. Then copy the data from the source bucket into the new bucket. To use the same bucket name in the destination Region you must be able to delete the source bucket before creating the new bucket." />
</node>
