<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_103787435" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Locking Objects Using Amazon S3 Object Lock. With Amazon S3 object lock you can store objects using a write-once-read-many (WORM) model. You can use it to prevent an object from being deleted or overwritten for a fixed amount of time or indefinitely." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631111" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_331288867" LINK="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/UsingMetadata.html" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Object Key and Metadata - Amazon Simple Storage Service">
<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_1160784230" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Object Key and Metadata. Each Amazon S3 object has data a key and metadata. The object key (or key name) uniquely identifies the object in a bucket. Object metadata is a set of name-value pairs. You can set object metadata at the time you upload it." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631111" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1032174127" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/s3-403-upload-bucket/" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="Troubleshoot 403 Errors When Adding Objects to S3 Buckets">
<node CREATED="1576216631111" ID="ID_612554034" MODIFIED="1576216631111" TEXT="If the IAM user is uploading objects to Amazon S3 using an Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (Amazon EC2) instance and that instance is routed to Amazon S3 using a VPC endpoint you must check the VPC endpoint policy. Be sure that the endpoint policy allows uploads to your bucket." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_160398947" LINK="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/object-lifecycle-mgmt.html" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Object Lifecycle Management - Amazon Simple Storage Service">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_275982" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Object Lifecycle Management. To manage your objects so that they are stored cost effectively throughout their lifecycle configure their lifecycle. A lifecycle configuration is a set of rules that define actions that Amazon S3 applies to a group of objects. There are two types of actions:" />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1434537840" LINK="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/dev/object-tagging.html" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Object Tagging - Amazon Simple Storage Service">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_132026296" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="You can use Amazon S3 batch operations through the AWS Management Console AWS CLI AWS SDKs or REST API. For more information see The Basics: Amazon S3 Batch Operations Jobs. API Operations Related to Object Tagging. Amazon S3 supports the following API operations that are specifically for object tagging: Object API Operations" />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1952376735" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/features/" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Object Storage Features &#226;&#8364;&#8220; Amazon S3">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_70621488" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="With a few clicks in the Amazon S3 Management Console you can apply the S3 Block Public Access settings to all buckets within your AWS account or to specific S3 buckets. Once the settings are applied to an AWS account any existing or new buckets and objects associated with that account inherit the settings that prevent public access. S3 Block " />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1782110329" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/premiumsupport/knowledge-center/decrypt-kms-encrypted-objects-s3/" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Download a KMS-Encrypted Object from Amazon S3">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_33368688" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="When a user sends a GET request Amazon S3 checks if the AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) user or role that sent the request is authorized to decrypt the key associated with the object. If the IAM user or role belongs to the same AWS account as the key then the permission to decrypt must be granted on the AWS KMS key&#226;&#8364;&#8482;s policy." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_545505777" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/s3/" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Cloud Object Storage - aws.amazon.com">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_113387340" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Amazon S3 provides easy-to-use management features so you can organize your data and configure finely-tuned access controls to meet your specific business organizational and compliance requirements. Amazon S3 is designed for 99.999999999% (11 9s) of durability and stores data for millions of applications for companies all around the world." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1205917686" LINK="https://intellipaat.com/blog/what-is-amazon-s3/" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="What is Amazon S3 tutorial - Creating a AWS S3 bucket ">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_578045975" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Amazon S3 is a storage that can be maintained and accessed over the Internet. In this Amazon S3 tutorial you will learn about what is Amazon S3 and its concepts how to create an AWS S3 bucket and more." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_419899064" LINK="https://aws.amazon.com/backup-restore/use-cases/" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Cloud Backup Designs | Amazon Web Services">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_1855529993" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Amazon S3 offers cross-region replication (CRR) which makes it simple to replicate S3 objects into other AWS Regions for reduced latency compliance security multi-region backup and disaster recovery. The metadata access controls and object tags associated to the source S3 object are also part of the replication." />
</node>
<node CREATED="1576216631112" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_905450698" LINK="https://www.cloudconformity.com/knowledge-base/aws/CloudTrail/s3-bucket-object-lock-enabled.html" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Enable Object Lock for CloudTrail S3 Buckets - CloudTrail ">
<node CREATED="1576216631112" ID="ID_315309053" MODIFIED="1576216631112" TEXT="Ensure that the Amazon S3 buckets associated with your CloudTrail trails have Object Lock feature enabled in order to prevent the objects they store (i.e. trail log files) from being deleted and meet regulatory compliance." />
</node>
